{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":6},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5},"Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434","","2002","\u003Cspan>L. Gentile, «Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434», \u003Ci>Epigraphica\u003C/i> 64 (2002): 224–29\u003C/span>",[7],{"file":8,"uri":8,"title":9,"status":10,"editionAuthor":12,"type":13,"objectType":17,"material":21,"condition":3,"layoutDesc":25,"handNote":32,"date":122,"places":127,"geo":136,"provenance":129,"provenanceGeo":140,"country":143,"region":144,"settlement":133,"repository":145,"idno":149,"textLang":152,"tmNumber":156,"facsimile":157,"letterHeights":164,"publications":165,"zotero":174,"keywords":183,"html":193,"bibl":194},"ISic001259","Statue base in honour of Olympis Mestos",{"_":11},"draft",null,{"_":14,"ana":15,"ref":16},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":18,"ana":19,"ref":20},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":22,"ana":23,"ref":24},"breccia","#material.stone.breccia","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/73.html",{"layout":26},{"p":27,"rs":28,"damage":3},"The inscription is set out over four lines on the front face of the block on its upper half. The text is roughly centred, lines 1-3 filling the face, line 4 a single word approximately centered. Spacing between words is apparent and increases significantly in line 3.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":33,"dimensions":110},[34,35],"The letters are regular and with terminal points rather than serfis, and are inscribed in parts in what is almost a punch style, rather than a chiselled groove. Alpha has broken bar; epsilon has mostly equal legnth cross-bars; theta has a full-width cross bar; kappa has full length bars; mu has vertical first and last, three-quarter length mid-strokes; omi